Explanation:

We use a dynamic programming approach to solve the problem. We create a 2D array dp to store the maximum points that can be obtained by choosing to solve or skip questions i and j. We initialize dp[i][j] to Math.max(questions[i][0], questions[j][1], which represents the maximum points between solving question i or skipping question j.

We iterate through the array to find the maximum points by comparing the maximum points from the previous iterations. The time complexity is O(n^2), where n is the number of questions. The space complexity is also O(n^2) due to the 2D array used for dynamic programming. The energy implications are low since the algorithm only requires a moderate amount of energy to solve the problem.

